The paper discusses the use of computational models of emotion in reinforcement learning agents and robots. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which includes topics related to machine learning and decision-making. The paper also focuses on robots, which suggests the category cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses learning efficiency, which is related to topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions human-robot interaction, which falls under the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Lastly, the paper discusses affective modeling, which is related to topics in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
